        <p>
            Point Blank Submissions is one of Ireland’s original Mixed Martial Arts and Brazilian Jiu Jitsu clubs, founded in 2002. 
            It began as a training club affiliated to SBG under John Kavanagh based in NUIG, extending from the NUIG Taekwon-Do club.
            Its founding members included first generation Irish MMA fighters such as Mark Leonard, Vinny Connelly, Tom Haddock and 
            Mark O’Toole. We moved to our first full-time premises in 2006 in the Parkmore Business Park where the club was run by 
            Mark Leonard. In February 2011 Mark stepped aside and Tim Murphy took over as head coach. In May 2011 we moved to our new 
            facility in the Glenrock Business Park in the Ballybane Industrial Estate.
      </p>
